The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parenthesis and prices are from
the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index gained 176.28, or 0.5
percent, to 32,836.23 at the 5 p.m. close of trading in
Johannesburg on April 29. South African equity markets were
closed yesterday for Workersâ€™ Day.  IFCA Technologies Ltd. (IFC)  : The investment company
with interests in software solutions and services said its
annual loss widened to 10.1 million rand ($1.5 million) from 2
million rand a year earlier. Shares in the company closed
unchanged at 8 cents.  Sovereign Food Investments (SOV)  Ltd: The poultry
producer said net income for the 12 months through February
climbed to 27.1 million rand from 11.1 million rand a year
earlier. Shares in Sovereign were unchanged at 5.26 rand.  Trustco Group Holdings Ltd. (TTO)  : The property
development and financial services group said earnings for the
12 months to March 31 are expected to increase by between 25
percent and 35 percent compared with a year earlier. Trustco
shares advanced 3.9 percent to 1.35 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
